Common ¬∂

The common subpackage provides generic/common parts for assembling the frameworks various components.

More domain specific concepts are introduced above the core base layer. The ID cache is implemented, a base Clock with Test and Live implementations which can control many Timer instances.

Trading domain specific components for generating Order and Identifier objects, common logging components, a high performance Queue and UUID4 factory.

The Actor class allows traders to implement their own customized components.

A user can inherit from Actor and optionally override any of the ‚Äúon‚Äù named event methods. The class is not entirely initialized in a stand-alone way, the intended usage is to pass actors to a Trader so that they can be fully ‚Äúwired‚Äù into the platform. Exceptions will be raised if an Actor attempts to operate without a managing Trader instance.

Bases: Component

The base class for all actor components.

Parameters :

Raises :

TypeError ‚Äì If config is not of type ActorConfig .

Warning

This class should not be used directly, but through a concrete subclass.

degrade ( self ) ‚Üí void ¬∂

Degrade the component.

While executing on_degrade() any exception will be logged and reraised, then the component will remain in a DEGRADING state.

Warning

Do not override.

If the component is not in a valid state from which to execute this method, then the component state will not change, and an error will be logged.

deregister_warning_event ( self , type event ) ‚Üí void ¬∂

Deregister the given event type from warning log levels.

Parameters :

event ( type ) ‚Äì The event class to deregister.

dispose ( self ) ‚Üí void ¬∂

Dispose of the component.

While executing on_dispose() any exception will be logged and reraised, then the component will remain in a DISPOSING state.

Warning

Do not override.

If the component is not in a valid state from which to execute this method, then the component state will not change, and an error will be logged.

fault ( self ) ‚Üí void ¬∂

Fault the component.

Calling this method multiple times has the same effect as calling it once (it is idempotent). Once called, it cannot be reversed, and no other methods should be called on this instance.

While executing on_fault() any exception will be logged and reraised, then the component will remain in a FAULTING state.

Warning

Do not override.

If the component is not in a valid state from which to execute this method, then the component state will not change, and an error will be logged.

set_timer ( self, unicode name, timedelta interval, datetime start_time=None, datetime stop_time=None, callback: Optional[Callable[[TimeEvent], None]] = None ) ‚Üí void ¬∂

Set a timer to run.

The timer will run from the start time (optionally until the stop time). When the intervals are reached the handlers will be passed the TimeEvent containing the timers unique name. If no handler is passed then the default handler (if registered) will receive the TimeEvent .

Parameters :

  • name ( str ) ‚Äì The name for the timer (must be unique for this clock).

  • interval ( timedelta ) ‚Äì The time interval for the timer.

  • start_time ( datetime , optional ) ‚Äì The start time for the timer (if None then starts immediately).

  • stop_time ( datetime , optional ) ‚Äì The stop time for the timer (if None then repeats indefinitely).

  • callback ( Callable [ [ TimeEvent ] , None ] , optional ) ‚Äì The callback to receive time events.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If name is not a valid string.

  • KeyError ‚Äì If name is not unique for this clock.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If interval is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If stop_time is not None and stop_time < time now.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If stop_time is not None and start_time + interval > stop_time .

  • TypeError ‚Äì If handler is not of type Callable or None .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If handler is None and no default handler is registered.

Component ¬∂

class Component ( Clock clock , Logger logger , TraderId trader_id=None , Identifier component_id=None , unicode component_name=None , MessageBus msgbus=None , dict config=None ) ¬∂

Bases: object

The base class for all system components.

A component is not considered initialized until a message bus is registered (this either happens when one is passed to the constructor, or when registered with a trader).

Thus, if the component does not receive a message bus through the constructor, then it will be in a PRE_INITIALIZED state, otherwise if one is passed then it will be in an INITIALIZED state.

Parameters :

  • clock ( Clock ) ‚Äì The clock for the component.

  • logger ( Logger ) ‚Äì The logger for the component.

  • trader_id ( TraderId , optional ) ‚Äì The trader ID associated with the component.

  • component_id ( Identifier , optional ) ‚Äì The component ID. If None is passed then the identifier will be taken from type(self).__name__ .

  • component_name ( str , optional ) ‚Äì The custom component name.

  • msgbus ( MessageBus , optional ) ‚Äì The message bus for the component (required before initialized).

  • config ( dict [ str , Any ] , optional ) ‚Äì The configuration for the component.

Raises :

ValueError ‚Äì If component_name is not a valid string.

Warning

This class should not be used directly, but through a concrete subclass.

class Queue ( int maxsize=0 ) ¬∂

Bases: object

Provides a high-performance stripped back queue for use with coroutines and an event loop.

If maxsize is less than or equal to zero, the queue size is infinite. If it is an integer greater than 0, then ‚Äúawait put()‚Äù will block when the queue reaches maxsize, until an item is removed by get().

Unlike the standard library Queue , you can reliably know this Queue‚Äôs size with qsize(), since your single-threaded asyncio application won‚Äôt be interrupted between calling qsize() and doing an operation on the Queue .

Parameters :

maxsize ( int ) ‚Äì The maximum capacity of the queue before blocking.

Warning

This queue is not thread-safe and must be called from the same thread as the event loop.

count ¬∂

The current count of items on the queue.

Returns :

int

empty ( self ) ‚Üí bool ¬∂

Return a value indicating whether the queue is empty.

Returns :

bool ‚Äì True if the queue is empty, False otherwise.

full ( self ) ‚Üí bool ¬∂

Return a value indicating whether the queue is full.

Returns :

bool ‚Äì True if there are maxsize items in the queue.

Notes

If the Queue was initialized with maxsize=0 (the default), then full() is never True.

class Throttler ( unicode name, int limit, timedelta interval, Clock clock, Logger logger, output_send: Callable[[Any], None], output_drop: Optional[Callable[[Any], None]] = None ) ¬∂

Bases: object

Provides a generic throttler which can either buffer or drop messages.

Will throttle messages to the given maximum limit-interval rate. If an output_drop handler is provided, then will drop messages which would exceed the rate limit. Otherwise will buffer messages until within the rate limit, then send.

Parameters :

  • name ( str ) ‚Äì The unique name of the throttler.

  • limit ( int ) ‚Äì The limit setting for the throttling.

  • interval ( timedelta ) ‚Äì The interval setting for the throttling.

  • clock ( Clock ) ‚Äì The clock for the throttler.

  • logger ( Logger ) ‚Äì The logger for the throttler.

  • output_send ( Callable [ [ Any ] , None ] ) ‚Äì The output handler to send messages from the throttler.

  • output_drop ( Callable [ [ Any ] , None ] , optional ) ‚Äì The output handler to drop messages from the throttler. If None then messages will be buffered.

Raises :

  • ValueError ‚Äì If name is not a valid string.

  • ValueError ‚Äì If limit is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If interval is not positive (> 0).

  • ValueError ‚Äì If output_send is not of type Callable .

  • ValueError ‚Äì If output_drop is not of type Callable or None .

Warning

This throttler is not thread-safe and must be called from the same thread as the event loop.

The internal buffer queue is unbounded and so a bounded queue should be upstream.

The interval for the throttler rate.

Returns :

timedelta

Returns :

bool

The limit for the throttler rate.

Returns :

int

The name of the throttler.

Returns :

str

Returns :
